# RabbitMQ scoped user for the audittrace-content-control sibling.
# ADR-057 PR-B2.5.
#
# This user has vhost-scoped permissions (set by the topology
# bootstrap Job at install time):
#   configure: ""                              (no exchange/queue creation)
#   write:     ^audittrace\.scan\.(verdicts|audit)$  (publish verdicts/audit only)
#   read:      ^audittrace\.scan\.requests$    (consume scan-requests only)
#
# 1. Generate a strong password (`openssl rand -base64 32`).
# 2. Save as ./secrets/rabbitmq_content_control_password.txt.
# 3. Run `make k8s-bootstrap-secrets`. Lands at:
#    - Vault: kv/audittrace/content-control/rabbitmq (key: password)
#    - k8s Secret: <release>-rabbitmq-content-control
#      (rendered by templates/secrets/secret-rabbitmq-content-control.yaml)
#    The audittrace-content-control sibling chart's Vault Agent
#    annotations source this path at pod startup.
REPLACE_WITH_STRONG_PASSWORD
